<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>be at someone’s service • be in someone’s service</xh5><p> <i>be at someone’s service—</i>1. be ready to help or assist a person: I <u>am at your service</u> whenever you should need my advice. 2. <i>(of things)</i> be at smb.’s disposal or ready to be used: My car <u>is at your service</u> to take you around Rome and its surroundings.</p><p> <div class="note">Note</div> The expression is not equivalent in meaning to the phrase <b>be of service to someone</b>—be helpful to a person: On many occasions he <u>was of service to</u> me, always in kindly, unobtrusive ways.</p><p> <i>be in someone’s service—</i>be working as smb.’s domestic servant: Miss White has <u>been in our service</u> for five years.</p> </entry>
